Plan: kube-greencosts Kubernetes Controller
TL;DR: Build an Operator SDK controller with 3 CRDs under greencosts.hstr.nl, a pluggable provider layer, and reconcilers that handle energy price scraping, energy-optimal job scheduling, and namespace hibernation.

Phase 1: Project Scaffolding
go.mod — module github.com/tristanscholten/kube-greencosts, Go 1.23; deps: controller-runtime v0.20, k8s.io/* v0.32, robfig/cron/v3, prometheus/client_golang, samber/oops
PROJECT — Operator SDK metadata (domain: greencosts.hstr.nl, layout: go.kubebuilder.io/v4)
Makefile — generate, manifests, build, run, docker-build, deploy targets using controller-gen
.gitignore
Phase 2: API Types (api/v1alpha1/)
groupversion_info.go — SchemeBuilder, GroupVersion = greencosts.hstr.nl/v1alpha1
energypricesource_types.go:
Spec: Provider, BiddingZone, Currency, RefreshSchedule (cron string), CacheTTL (metav1.Duration), CustomProviderConfig (URL + SecretKeySelector for bearer auth)
Status: LastUpdated, Prices []PriceInterval{Start, End metav1.Time, EurPerMWh float64}, Conditions
energyawarecronjob_types.go:
Spec: EnergyPriceSource (LocalObjectReference), Deadline/EarliestStart/LatestStart (HH:MM strings), TimeZone, SchedulePolicy{PriceWeight float64, AvoidPeakHours, PreferNegativePrices bool}, Fallback{RunAt, WhenPriceDataMissing}, JobTemplate batchv1.JobTemplateSpec
Status: NextScheduledTime *metav1.Time, LastJobRef *corev1.ObjectReference, Conditions
hibernatepolicy_types.go:
Spec: Selector{NamespaceSelector metav1.LabelSelector}, IdleDetection{NoIngressRequestsFor, CPUBelow, NetworkBelow, IgnoreDuring []IgnorePeriod{Weekdays, From, Until, Timezone}}, Action{ScaleDeploymentsToZero, SnapshotPVCs bool} (no wakeOnHttp)
Status: HibernatedNamespaces []string, Conditions
zz_generated.deepcopy.go — DeepCopyObject + DeepCopyInto for all types (output of make generate)
Phase 3: Provider Layer (internal/providers/)
interface.go — EnergyProvider interface with FetchPrices(ctx, FetchPricesRequest) ([]PriceInterval, error), plus a Registry (map of name → factory)
custom/provider.go — HTTP GET to configured URL; optional Authorization: Bearer from referenced k8s Secret; parses [{"start":"...","end":"...","eurPerMWh":...}]; uses slog + samber/oops
Phase 4: Controllers (internal/controller/)
energypricesource_controller.go:
Check cache validity (lastUpdated + cacheTTL > now)
Parse cron via robfig/cron/v3, skip if next fire time not yet reached
Look up provider from registry, call FetchPrices, patch status
RequeueAfter(durationUntilNextCronFire)
energyawarecronjob_controller.go:
Watch EnergyAwareCronJob + its referenced EnergyPriceSource
Filter prices to [earliestStart, latestStart] window for next day in configured timezone
Score each 30-min slot: score = eurPerMWh × priceWeight; bonus for negative prices, penalty for peak hours
If no prices and whenPriceDataMissing=true → use fallback.runAt
Store nextScheduledTime in status; RequeueAfter(durationUntilThen)
When requeue fires: create batchv1.Job from jobTemplate with owner ref; update lastJobRef; requeue for tomorrow
hibernatepolicy_controller.go:
List matching namespaces; check current time against all ignoreDuring windows
In window → scale hibernated deployments back to original replicas (stored as greencosts.hstr.nl/original-replicas annotation); RequeueAfter(window-end)
Outside window → query metrics-server for pod CPU; query Prometheus for network I/O + ingress RPS; if all idle thresholds exceeded → annotate + scale deployments to 0; optionally create VolumeSnapshot per PVC if snapshotPVCs=true
Phase 5: Metrics Client (internal/metrics/client.go)
MetricsClient interface: QueryCPU(ctx, namespace) using k8s.io/metrics; QueryNetworkIngress(ctx, namespace, window) using prometheus/client_golang against a configurable Prometheus URL
Phase 6: Entry Point (cmd/manager/main.go)
Flags: --prometheus-url, --leader-elect, health/metrics bind addresses
Register schemes (core + batch + greencosts v1alpha1)
Build provider registry, metrics client
Wire all three reconcilers
mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())
Phase 7: Config/Manifests (config/)
17–19. CRD YAML for each of the 3 kinds (hand-written, matches Go types; make manifests regenerates)
20–22. ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, ServiceAccount — covers CRDs, deployments, jobs, pods, secrets, namespaces, volumesnapshots, metrics API
23. config/manager/manager.yaml — Deployment for the controller
24. config/default/kustomization.yaml

Relevant files: All new — 24 files total listed in the plan doc.

Verification:

go build tristanscholten. compiles clean
go vet tristanscholten. passes
kubectl apply -f config/crd/bases/ installs all 3 CRDs without errors
httptest.NewServer stub for custom provider → EnergyPriceSource reconcile populates status correctly
Scheduling algorithm unit tests: no prices → fallback; negative price with preferNegativePrices=true → selected
HibernatePolicy ignore-window logic: assert no scale-down during business hours
Excluded scope: wake-on-HTTP, admission webhooks, multi-cluster, CI pipeline, go.sum (run go mod tidy)